Static Dispatch: Static dispatch refers to the process of determining which function or method to call at compile-time, based on the declared type of the variable or object. In simpler terms, it’s like deciding what action to take when you know exactly what type of thing you’re dealing with.
For example, if you have a Swift function that adds two numbers:
func add(\_ a: Int, \_ b: Int) -&gt; Int { return a + b } And you call it like this:
